				<baseName xml:lang="en">Citric Acid</baseName>
				<baseName xml:lang="zh">柠檬酸</baseName>
			</name>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">枸橼酸 、3-羧基-3-羟基戊二酸、2-羟基丙烷-1,2,3-三羧酸</common:synonyms>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="zh">枸橼酸 、3-羧基-3-羟基戊二酸、2-羟基丙烷-1,2,3-三羧酸</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification name="ILCD 1.1" classes="../ILCDClassification.xml">
					<common:class level="0">Materials production</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Organic chemicals</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<CASNumber>77-92-9</CASNumber>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Citric acid is a versatile additive for food, beverages, medicines, and dietary supplements, as well as cleaning and disinfecting products. It is an organic compound found in high amounts in citrus fruits, giving lemons and limes their distinctive sour taste. Many manufacturers add citric acid to packaged foods and beverages to keep them fresh. It is a common additive because of its many benefits and minimal environmental impact. It is a colourless crystalline organic compound belonging to the family of carboxylic acids, present in practically all plants and in many animal tissues and fluids.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">柠檬酸是一种用途广泛的添加剂，可用于食品、饮料、药品、膳食补充剂以及清洁和消毒产品。它是一种有机化合物，大量存在于柑橘类水果中，赋予柠檬和酸橙独特的酸味。许多制造商在包装食品和饮料中添加柠檬酸以保持新鲜。它是一种常见的添加剂，因为它有许多好处，而且对环境的影响很小。柠檬酸是一种无色结晶有机化合物，属于羧酸家族，几乎存在于所有植物以及许多动物组织和体液中。</common:generalComment>
			<sumFormula>C₆H₈O₇</sumFormula>
